blog.name: jazzienuggets
blog.title: Remember Kindness In The Hardest Times!

summary: There is still time for 2018 to end on a happier note!
title: There is still time for 2018 to end on a happier note!
body:
It’s been a while since I’ve posted so I thought I’d better change that. 

My last post was a last attempt at getting noticed by @taylorswift before her concert in Melbourne. Did it work? No! I was lucky enough to spot MUMMA SWIFT walk past my row 3 times but didn’t get close enough to meet her. But seeing her was one of those crazy moments when I thought I had a hope in hell of meeting Taylor at the concert coming true. It wasn’t to be at that point in time and while I wish I’d gotten the pleasure, it’s all ok! Other than that, the concert was ABSOLUTELY EPIC!!!! I constantly replay the videos I took on my phone and while I attended the concert on my own, I got seated next to 2 mother/daughter duo’s and it was like we were all friends through the concert. I’e truly never experienced this sense of community before! @taylorswift You and you’re music have an ability to draw together people who understand you and back you on a level a lot of others laugh at. We’ve faced criticism, rumours, happiness, deep depression, anxiety that makes your body shake and so much more in a unique way. That is something so special and rare! 

So on my way home from the concert I drove past a woman literally metres from my house passed out on the side of the street. I got out to help her and she was luckily ok (had crashed her skateboard into the gutter at 1am) and someone came to help her home. It has definitely been one of the most memorable moments of the year. 

Since then, I discovered one of my nieces has become traumatised by photos she was shown of my car after the crash and is too scared to get in my new car. This is actually one of the most deeply sad things to come to terms with. I am still having dreams about having a car crash which makes everything even worse. 

I thought (and still have hope) things were looking up when I got offered a full-time role in residential care. My first full-time counselling based role since graduating!!!! But I found out about this 7 weeks ago and there have been a lot of admin based problems that have delayed my training and general stat date. But because I got this offer, I left my previous job a week before the initial start date I was given but then that fell through and beginning the 4th week after that I’m still waiting for something concrete to work with. 

Coming up to Christmas, not much money…I’m not loving how the rest of 2018 is looking. But I still have HOPE!
